title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1989-10-18
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street, Little Red Rooster, Peggy-O, Queen Jane Approximately, Bird Song, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Ship of Fools, Women Are Smarter, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> All Along The Watchtower-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Understand I don't understand why no one reviews these incredible shows and  matts work. Guess were all to busy. Think about the time at that show. The time that will never happen again. How did it effect your your life.did we go to shows for a reason? What was it. I know I went to connect with all the heads in the venue. All of us with the same exact thought at the same time. THATS powerful shit.the music of course and watching our favorite musicians. At the time but damn. It should mean more to people to take three minutes to say something about it. Its important to me if its not to you then you ain't in the club. Peace and love.
